---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Kitchen Renovations Tuggeranong | 1980s–90s Family Homes"
  description="Kitchen renovations in Tuggeranong — full renovations and open-plan reconfigurations for the south's 1980s–90s family homes, with custom cabinetry and stone benchtops. ACT-licensed. Free quote."
  canonical="https://kitchenrenovationscanberra.com.au/tuggeranong/"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Tuggeranong &middot; Kambah &middot; Wanniassa &middot; Greenway &middot; Calwell</span>
      <h1>Kitchen renovations in <span class="accent">Tuggeranong</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Tuggeranong is Canberra&rsquo;s big southern district &mdash; 1980s and
        90s family homes where the original kitchen is closed off and overdue.
        We open them up: full renovations, open-plan reconfigurations, custom
        cabinetry and compliant stone benchtops built for family life.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Tuggeranong</span>
      <h2>The Tuggeranong kitchen story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>1980s&ndash;90s family homes, closed-off kitchens.</h3>
        <p>
          Tuggeranong filled out through the 1980s and 90s &mdash; Kambah,
          Wanniassa, Calwell, Gowrie, Monash, Bonython and the Greenway town
          centre &mdash; with three- and four-bedroom family homes on generous
          blocks. The kitchens of that era are typically <strong>closed off</strong>
          from the living and dining rooms and feel dated and cramped by modern
          standards. Opening them into a single family living space is the
          renovation we do most across the district.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Open-plan reconfiguration done right.</h3>
        <p>
          Turning a separate 90s kitchen into an open-plan hub usually means
          removing a wall &mdash; and in these homes it&rsquo;s often load-bearing.
          That brings structural beams and likely <strong>ACTPLA building
          approval</strong> into the job. We <a href="/services/kitchen-design/">design</a>
          the new flow in 3D, get the structural and approval side right, and
          rebuild with an island, a <a href="/services/custom-cabinetry/">custom
          cabinetry</a> layout and a <a href="/services/benchtops/">stone
          benchtop</a> that suits a busy household.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Built for families &mdash; storage and durability.</h3>
        <p>
          Tuggeranong is family country, so the brief is nearly always about
          storage and hard-wearing finishes: deep pot drawers, a generous pantry,
          a durable benchtop that survives kids and homework, and a layout that
          handles the after-school rush. Porcelain and granite benchtops are
          popular here for exactly that reason &mdash; tough, heat- and
          stain-resistant, and fully compliant after the 2024 engineered-stone
          ban.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Asbestos checks on the older stock.</h3>
        <p>
          The earliest Tuggeranong homes edge into the period where bonded
          asbestos can appear in wall sheeting, floor backing and old splashbacks,
          and the ACT carries the Mr Fluffy loose-fill asbestos legacy
          (1968&ndash;1980). On any home of that vintage we identify suspect
          materials and arrange licensed testing and removal before demolition.
          We never disturb material we suspect contains asbestos.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Tuggeranong kitchen jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Full renovation opening a closed 1990s Kambah kitchen to open-plan living ($32K&ndash;$58K)</li>
          <li>Island kitchen with custom cabinetry and a porcelain benchtop in Wanniassa</li>
          <li>Family-focused storage upgrade &mdash; pantry, pot drawers, durable benchtop</li>
          <li>Budget makeover on a sound 90s kitchen before selling (from ~$8,800)</li>
          <li>Open-plan reconfiguration with load-bearing wall removal and ACTPLA approval</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/belconnen/">Belconnen</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/gungahlin/">Gungahlin</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/woden/">Woden</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/dickson/">Dickson</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/canberra-region/">All Canberra &amp; the ACT</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Tuggeranong kitchen quote.</h2>
        <p>Open-plan family renovations. Storage-smart layouts, durable benchtops, fixed-price quotes.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
